1. Intel DRI will be disabled as a result of applying the vgaarb patch.
2. Config is applicable to Intel IGD (Primary) and GTS 450 (Secondary, GF116.rom file is the ROM file dump)
   Kernel 4.9.24 + acs patch+ vgaarb patch on Ubuntu 16.04.
3. This configuration works only ONCE, a host system reboot is required to launch the VM for the second time.
4. It was necessary to remove the nvidia driver, since it was quirky to disable it before it would snatch the gpu.
